      "comment": "BLUE ENERGY (8) comes off an average performance last start when sixth at Gawler over 400m behind Oregon Hutan (23.47) in a Grade 5. Can make amends. SHAKA GOES BANG (2) is a talented type and proved too classy last time to win by 2 lengths at this track in a handy 19.81 beating Deep Purple. The form from his last run stacks up well. Form should stack up. ALLINGA ALAN (1) produced a moderate run last time when fifth at Mt Gambier over 400m behind Pinky Rocks (23.48) in a Grade 6. Some good form is emerging from his last run. Cannot be underestimated. HE'S NO DIVA (4) can fill a top-three spot.",
